    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-07-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-07-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="802"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d802">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Terrell</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-07-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 10, 1896.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1018.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I inclose for your information copy of a
                        letter<note n="1" xml:id="d802fn1">Not printed.</note> from R. D. Kimball
                    concerning the protection of his sister, Dr. Grace Kimball, and her associates
                    at Van.</p>
                <p>Mr. Kimball has been assured that you fully appreciate the situation at Van, and
                    will afford all possible protection to American citizens residing there.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Richard Olney.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
